import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['normal'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Normal values')
    plt.axvline(data['normal'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['normal'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Normal values')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title("What is the distribution of 'normal' values in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['day'])]

    plt.plot(data['day'], data['actual'], label='Actual', color='blue')
    plt.plot(data['day'], data['forecast'], label='Forecast', color='orange')
    plt.title("How does the 'actual' value compare to the 'forecast' value?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Day')
    plt.ylabel('Values')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
